        "text": "B-1 For a given it, no more than three different values of (x) are possible (four would require one part each of size at least 1,2,3,4, and that's already more than 9 elements). If no such x, y exist, each pair (П(x), П' (х)) occurs for at most 1 element of x, and since there are only 3 x 3 possible pairs, each must occur exactly once. In particular, each value of (x) must occur 3 times. However, clearly any given value of n(x) occurs kn(x) times, where k is the number of distinct partitions of that size. Thus n(x) can occur 3 times only if it equals 1 or 3, but we have three distinct values for which it occurs, contradiction.",
