        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A position is a win for the player to move if and only if it has a nonzero value, in which case the winning strategy is to always move to a 0 position. (This is always possible from a nonzero position and never from a zero position, which is precisely the condition that defines the set of winning positions.) In this case, the winning move is to reduce the pile of 3 down to 2, and you can easily describe the entire strategy if you so desire.",
