        "text": "B-3 For n = 1 we obviously get 45, while for n = 3 the answer is 0 because it both changes sign (because determinants are alternating) and remains unchanged (by symmetry) when you switch any two rows other than the first one. So only n = 2 is left. By the multilinearity of the determinant, the answer is the determinant of the matrix whose first (resp. second) row is the sum of all possible first (resp. second) rows. There are 90 first rows whose sum is the vector (450,405), and 100 second rows whose sum is (450,450). Thus the answer is 450 × 450 - 450 × 405 = 45 × 450 = 20250.",
